Cafe Aria has got to have the most amazing Stromboli I've ever eaten. Their Bakery is second-to-none considering it's essentially a corporate Cafe serving local government Staffing contractors. Would definitely recommend!

Favorite quick eats in Washington. They make a breakfast stromboli with bacon or sausage. I've never seen one before. Amazingly good and inexpensive! Air conditioned dining area. Diet Coke on tap! Yay!

The cafe is located in  great spot. From the corner of the passport office. It is quite welcoming. They have a system set up to make and provide the food quickly to the customers. The ladies looked ready and motivated. The seating arrangement was arranged to maximize the space usage. My egg and cheese sandwich on rye was really delicious. Definitely recommend it. If wondering why I didn't give a five, I always think there's room for improvement, whether its price, etc.

Typically this hasn't been too bad for a quick visit, though when ordering off-menu they just can't seem to get it right (this isn't to say for all staff). I get the basic egg and Swiss cheese with mayo on wheat breakfast sandwich and it's always up in the air with how it comes. The pizzas and subs, however, are very good for what they are and there's always an abundance of coffee. If you stick to the overhead menu without any deviations the friendly staff are prompt and very friendly.

This is my favorite coffe shop and lunch stop.  I seldom miss a day at the restaurant and have never had a bad meal or an unpleasant experience.  The staff is very friendly and helpful and they have a wide variety of very tasty food.  Prices are very competitive for the area.  I highly recommend trying the Cafe Aria.
